  "prompt": "What are the 3 best things you would recommend to improve your questions on Quora?",
  "response": "Improving your questions on Quora can help you get better answers and engage more effectively with the community. Here are three recommendations:\n\n1. **Be Specific and Clear**:\n   - **Details**: Provide enough context and background information in your question. This helps respondents understand exactly what you're asking.\n   - **Focus**: Avoid overly broad or vague questions. Narrowing down the scope can lead to more precise and helpful answers.\n   - **Clarity**: Use clear and straightforward language. Ensure your question is easy to read and understand.\n\n2. **Research and Add Relevant Tags**:\n   - **Keywords**: Use relevant keywords and tags to classify your question appropriately. This makes it easier for people knowledgeable on the topic to find and answer your question.\n   - **Popular Tags**: Incorporate tags that are commonly used in your topic area. Popular tags attract more attention and responses.\n   - **Existing Questions**: Check if similar questions have already been asked and answered. You might glean valuable insights from existing responses or refine your question based on what's already there.\n\n3. **Engage with the Community**:\n   - **Follow-Up**: Be active in responding to answers and comments. Ask for clarification or further information if needed. Showing appreciation and engagement encourages more thoughtful responses.\n   - **Ask for Expertise**: Directly request insights from experts or individuals who have shown deep knowledge in the area. Personalizing your request can attract high-quality responses.\n   - **Politeness**: Maintain a courteous and respectful tone. A positive attitude fosters productive and constructive interactions.\n\nFollowing these recommendations can help enhance the quality and effectiveness of your questions on Quora.",
